Senate Resolution 13
By: Senators Mallow of the 2nd, Jones II of the 22nd and Jackson of the 41st
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Richard Coleman; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Richard Coleman has dedicated over 30 years to law enforcement as a Georgia
3 peace officer, earning certification as a Georgia law enforcement executive administrator and
4 serving in leadership roles such as chief of police, chief of internal affairs, assistant chief of
5 police, and police operations commander; and
6 WHEREAS, he has demonstrated extensive expertise in staffing, budgeting, policy creation,
7 outsourcing, resource management, and community engagement throughout his distinguished
8 career; and
9 WHEREAS, Richard Coleman is an honest and dedicated public servant who strives for
10 excellence in all of his endeavors and whose primary concern is the welfare and safety of the
11 citizens of Chatham County; and
12 WHEREAS, he is highly regarded by the citizens of his community and by state and local
13 government officials as a man of unquestioned integrity and dedication to the administration
14 of justice and sound principles of law enforcement; and
