15 WHEREAS, this spirited law enforcement professional has exhibited extraordinary devotion
16 to duty, outstanding loyalty, fine leadership, and meticulous attention to detail throughout
17 his exemplary career; and
18 WHEREAS, his inspiring commitment to the welfare of others stands as an outstanding
19 example of the positive effect law enforcement professionals have on the lives and
20 well-being of others; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that gratitude is expressed for the unique and
22 often unheralded contributions of local law enforcement professionals on behalf of the
23 citizens of this state.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
25 commend the care, courage, sympathy, and selfless dedication exhibited by Richard Coleman
26 in carrying out the difficult duties of his vocation and express their utmost appreciation for
27 having so purely and truly defined for others the meaning of public servant.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
29 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Richard Coleman.
